{
  "message": "test(harness): refresh inspector_hit_regions_with_panel snapshot after detail-panel rewrite\n\nRegenerates the ANSI golden snapshot for the inspector detail panel\nafter the commit that reworked it (`feat(widgets/inspector):\nselection-first detail panel with hit-region breakdown and render-time\nreadout`). The new panel draws each text span with its own background\nsentinel wrap (`[48;2;0;0;0m...[0m`) because `draw_panel_text` now\npasses through the clipped region more precisely, so the snapshot\npicks up the explicit style-switch escapes on every label line:\n\n    - \"Inspector\"\n    - \"Mode: Hit Regions\"\n    - \"Hover: (4,7)\"\n    - \"Region: Content\"\n    - \"ID: 2\"\n\nNo visible output change for a user looking at the terminal \u2014 this is\na pure encoding refresh of the golden file. Commit separately so bad\nsnapshot drift is easy to revert without touching the widget code.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>",
